metadata.name: Time to Fly
metadata.description:
Laser art created in LaserLewDude's closet using lasers, glass, mirrors and H2O. 

Not a render.

Setup details:

- 1W Lasercube x2 from sides going off 1st surface mirror suspended above, then down and back up again (violet/blue wide beams)  
•  
- Colorful lumia background from RGB going though bumpy glass (Lumia) refocused by 3 inch glass ball  
•  
- 488nm (pretty blue) going horizontally behind centerpiece - being reflected back by a corner cube retroreflector.   
•  
- 638nm (red) x2  single diode modules  
•  
505nm (water green) x2 single diode modules  
•  
- 488nm through star field diffraction grating for background
